1
00:00:51,040 --> 00:00:52,480
I'm just asking to crash
here for a little bit.

2
00:00:52,480 --> 00:00:54,440
Just until I can
head back to my country.

3
00:00:54,440 --> 00:00:57,000
Wow, Gift.
This place is way more livable.

4
00:00:57,000 --> 00:00:58,000
This looks so delicious!

5
00:00:58,000 --> 00:00:58,880
It tastes great.

6
00:00:58,880 --> 00:01:01,880
Chai...what if you end up
getting back with him?

7
00:01:02,720 --> 00:01:04,040
Technician Yoon...

8
00:01:04,040 --> 00:01:05,520
Does your airline
actually have a doctor?

9
00:01:05,520 --> 00:01:06,120
No.

10
00:01:06,120 --> 00:01:08,320
Doctor Yep, he just
hangs around us a lot.

11
00:01:08,320 --> 00:01:11,000
I bet Doctor Yep
is definitely the mole.

12
00:01:11,000 --> 00:01:12,320
Yeah, actually,
that makes sense.

13
00:01:12,320 --> 00:01:13,000
Come on, Yoon.

14
00:01:13,000 --> 00:01:14,360
We've got a bit of time
before the doctor gets back.

15
00:01:15,920 --> 00:01:16,920
Whoa!

16
00:01:19,120 --> 00:01:20,120
Please open the door for me!

17
00:01:21,520 --> 00:01:22,480
Ninja!

18
00:01:22,480 --> 00:01:23,480
Chai!

19
00:01:23,480 --> 00:01:25,240
Wait, you two know each other?

20
00:01:25,240 --> 00:01:26,280
- He's an ex.
- He's an ex.

21
00:01:26,280 --> 00:01:28,240
Then if he's that important to you,

22
00:01:28,240 --> 00:01:30,480
just go back and date him again!

23
00:01:30,480 --> 00:01:32,840
So, even if he were to show up
right at our doorstep...

24
00:01:32,840 --> 00:01:34,840
you wouldn't waver,
right, Chai?

25
00:01:39,360 --> 00:01:40,480
Ninja...

26
00:01:40,480 --> 00:01:41,480
Hey, Chai!

27
00:01:41,480 --> 00:01:42,600
Chai, don't!

28
00:01:42,600 --> 00:01:43,360
Wait, hold on!

29
00:01:43,360 --> 00:01:44,080
Don't! Don't go!

30
00:01:44,080 --> 00:01:44,800
Come back first!

31
00:01:44,800 --> 00:01:45,920
I thought you said
you wouldn't waver!

32
00:01:45,920 --> 00:01:46,920
Ninja...

33
00:01:52,320 --> 00:01:54,920
I know that my comeback...

34
00:01:54,920 --> 00:01:56,160
makes you feel uncomfortable.

35
00:01:56,160 --> 00:01:57,240
So you do realize it.

36
00:01:57,240 --> 00:01:59,360
It's not that hard to see,
it's obvious.

37
00:02:00,600 --> 00:02:01,440
Can you let go of Shiney first?

38
00:02:01,440 --> 00:02:02,240
Who the hell is Shiney?

39
00:02:02,240 --> 00:02:03,840
Is that your dog's name?

40
00:02:03,840 --> 00:02:05,280
It's my name.

41
00:02:05,280 --> 00:02:07,360
That's what Nin-Nin calls me.

42
00:02:07,360 --> 00:02:08,360
You guys even have pet names?

43
00:02:08,360 --> 00:02:09,480
Then you definitely shouldn't be
talking to each other!

44
00:02:09,480 --> 00:02:11,520
What if you end up
getting back together?

45
00:02:11,520 --> 00:02:12,920
I'm just asking to
crash here for a little bit.

46
00:02:12,920 --> 00:02:14,240
Just until I can
head back to my country.

47
00:02:14,240 --> 00:02:16,040
There are literally...

48
00:02:16,040 --> 00:02:18,640
26.8 million households
in Thailand...

49
00:02:18,640 --> 00:02:21,360
and you still asked
to stay at your ex's house?

50
00:02:21,360 --> 00:02:25,040
Shiney told me that if I ever
needed anything, I could just ask.

51
00:02:25,040 --> 00:02:27,480
Why on earth would you tell him that?

52
00:02:27,480 --> 00:02:29,000
But this is Tid-Gift's house too,
half of it is hers.

53
00:02:29,000 --> 00:02:30,920
Wouldn't you want to ask her first?

54
00:02:30,920 --> 00:02:32,320
But Tid-Gift used to say...

55
00:02:32,320 --> 00:02:33,480
that she loved having me over.

56
00:02:33,480 --> 00:02:34,520
When did she ever say that?

57
00:02:34,520 --> 00:02:35,560
You know, that night...

58
00:02:35,560 --> 00:02:37,480
right here on this sofa,
when we were...

59
00:02:39,400 --> 00:02:42,720
You're so hot,
why don't you just move in?

60
00:02:42,720 --> 00:02:46,040
When we were like...

61
00:02:47,920 --> 00:02:50,360
Fine, fine, fine! I said it.
Just drop it!

62
00:02:50,360 --> 00:02:51,400
Let's change the subject.

63
00:02:51,400 --> 00:02:52,520
Still, asking to stay with an ex...

64
00:02:52,520 --> 00:02:53,640
is just totally inappropriate,
don't you think?

65
00:02:53,640 --> 00:02:54,760
It's not like he has
a new partner or anything.

66
00:02:54,760 --> 00:02:56,240
Don't you think
you'll be a burden to them?

67
00:02:56,240 --> 00:02:57,680
How about we split
the expenses three ways?

68
00:02:57,680 --> 00:02:58,360
Sounds good.

69
00:02:58,360 --> 00:02:59,320
And when they go on flights,

70
00:02:59,320 --> 00:03:00,880
who's going to take care
of the house?

71
00:03:00,880 --> 00:03:01,600
Nobody.

72
00:03:01,600 --> 00:03:02,840
Well, shouldn't there be someone?

73
00:03:02,840 --> 00:03:03,680
I guess.

74
00:03:03,680 --> 00:03:04,400
Should it be a complete stranger...

75
00:03:04,400 --> 00:03:05,440
or someone familiar like an ex?

76
00:03:05,440 --> 00:03:06,240
An ex.

77
00:03:06,240 --> 00:03:07,040
Alright, so what's it gonna be?

78
00:03:07,040 --> 00:03:07,520
Okay, deal.

79
00:03:07,520 --> 00:03:08,520
Thank you.

80
00:03:08,520 --> 00:03:09,240
Hey, Chaba!

81
00:03:09,240 --> 00:03:09,800
Huh?

82
00:03:09,800 --> 00:03:10,640
Why did you just do?

83
00:03:10,640 --> 00:03:12,760
Hey, this guy is actually brilliant.

84
00:03:12,760 --> 00:03:14,040
I'll sleep in Shiney's room, okay?

85
00:03:14,120 --> 00:03:14,600
Whoa!

86
00:03:14,600 --> 00:03:16,480
Damn, that was fast.
Living up to his name, Ninja.

87
00:03:16,480 --> 00:03:17,880
Kree, go stop him!

88
00:03:17,880 --> 00:03:19,640
Hey, wait up!

89
00:03:21,240 --> 00:03:21,520
Whoa!

90
00:03:21,800 --> 00:03:22,320
Whoa!

91
00:03:23,080 --> 00:03:24,000
What the hell is this?

92
00:03:24,000 --> 00:03:25,480
I'll take this back.

93
00:03:25,480 --> 00:03:27,480
It's the tool of my trade.

94
00:03:27,480 --> 00:03:28,880
See you later, Shiney.

95
00:03:29,800 --> 00:03:30,960
What's up with your ex?

96
00:03:30,960 --> 00:03:32,040
Is he a cowboy or something?

97
00:03:32,040 --> 00:03:33,680
You'll find out soon enough.

98
00:03:34,560 --> 00:03:36,000
Now that he's staying here...

99
00:03:36,000 --> 00:03:37,840
you'll probably be seeing a lot of him.

100
00:03:37,840 --> 00:03:38,840
Nin-Nin...

101
00:03:49,400 --> 00:03:52,280
Technician Yoon might actually
be someone Pong sent over.

102
00:03:53,360 --> 00:03:55,080
I'm the closest one to him.

103
00:03:55,080 --> 00:03:57,120
Will he do something to me?

104
00:03:57,120 --> 00:04:00,400
Hey, last time,
Peck almost got us killed.

105
00:04:00,600 --> 00:04:03,560
This time, I might actually
end up as a dead body.

106
00:04:04,280 --> 00:04:06,400
Oh, I'm gonna go grab
some snacks. Want anything?

107
00:04:06,400 --> 00:04:07,040
I'll take one dead body.

108
00:04:07,040 --> 00:04:08,160
Huh?

109
00:04:08,640 --> 00:04:10,600
Nothing, I was thinking
about something else.

110
00:04:10,600 --> 00:04:11,320
A dead body?

111
00:04:11,320 --> 00:04:13,440
No, I meant the assassins.

112
00:04:13,440 --> 00:04:14,520
The assassins?

113
00:04:14,520 --> 00:04:15,400
What the hell is
wrong with you, Glasses?

114
00:04:15,400 --> 00:04:16,560
Have you lost your mind?

115
00:04:16,560 --> 00:04:18,200
Fine, I'm tired of playing along.

116
00:04:18,200 --> 00:04:19,360
Are you on the same side...

117
00:04:19,360 --> 00:04:22,440
as those assassin sisters,
Peck and Pong?

118
00:04:22,440 --> 00:04:25,040
You mean
Sergeant Peck and Captain Pong?

119
00:04:25,040 --> 00:04:26,880
These guys, right? Here.

120
00:04:28,160 --> 00:04:29,280
Isn't that a bit too much
of a coincidence?

121
00:04:29,280 --> 00:04:30,840
Anyone can be named
Peck or Pong, okay?

122
00:04:30,840 --> 00:04:32,640
If I happened to know
the assassins you're talking about...

123
00:04:32,640 --> 00:04:33,960
now that would be weird.

124
00:04:36,040 --> 00:04:37,720
By the way, what assassins?

125
00:04:38,480 --> 00:04:40,160
Right now, I still don't know
where they came from.

126
00:04:40,880 --> 00:04:42,200
I just know that...

127
00:04:42,200 --> 00:04:44,560
they're trying to destroy
Glamorous Airline...

128
00:04:44,560 --> 00:04:46,360
and also my mom's airline.

129
00:04:46,360 --> 00:04:48,280
But there's so little information.

130
00:04:48,600 --> 00:04:52,400
No one knows about
the evil shit they've been doing.

131
00:04:52,400 --> 00:04:54,560
No matter how hard it gets,

132
00:04:54,560 --> 00:04:56,880
I will find out who they really are.

133
00:04:58,480 --> 00:04:59,920
Are they scammers?

134
00:04:59,920 --> 00:05:02,440
No, it's way scarier than that.

135
00:05:02,440 --> 00:05:06,160
They are trying to hack
the airline's customer database.

136
00:05:06,160 --> 00:05:08,000
No, what I mean is,
they have guns!

137
00:05:08,000 --> 00:05:10,000
And they've been trying to kill us!

138
00:05:10,000 --> 00:05:11,720
Come here.

139
00:05:11,720 --> 00:05:14,160
Look. "Very little information."

140
00:05:14,160 --> 00:05:17,280
Scammers targeting
airline customer databases.

141
00:05:17,280 --> 00:05:19,640
Please contact 02-453-2548.

142
00:05:19,640 --> 00:05:21,920
You should save this number.

143
00:05:21,920 --> 00:05:25,640
Uh...it matches perfectly.

144
00:05:25,640 --> 00:05:27,960
Now you can leave it to the police...

145
00:05:27,960 --> 00:05:29,120
Detective Conan.

146
00:05:31,040 --> 00:05:33,600
Oh, All-New.

147
00:05:33,600 --> 00:05:36,640
Uh, Technician Yoon.

148
00:05:36,640 --> 00:05:39,720
I'll talk to Doctor Yep first...

149
00:05:39,720 --> 00:05:41,160
And I'll come back to see you later.

150
00:05:41,160 --> 00:05:42,080
Alright, alright.

151
00:05:42,080 --> 00:05:44,280
Let's continue, Miss Sky.

152
00:05:44,280 --> 00:05:46,680
Does your airline
actually have a doctor?

153
00:05:46,680 --> 00:05:48,080
No.

154
00:05:48,080 --> 00:05:51,240
Doctor Yep, he just
hangs around us a lot.

155
00:05:56,760 --> 00:05:59,240
Besides hanging around...

156
00:05:59,240 --> 00:06:00,760
what else did those assassins do?

157
00:06:00,760 --> 00:06:02,400
Shit, then who is "P"?

158
00:06:03,400 --> 00:06:06,480
He secretly infiltrated
our Line group chat.

159
00:06:06,480 --> 00:06:07,520
Miss Sky...

160
00:06:07,520 --> 00:06:08,440
I'll send all the details

161
00:06:08,440 --> 00:06:11,320
into the Line group later.

162
00:06:11,320 --> 00:06:13,120
Are you in our Line group too?

163
00:06:13,120 --> 00:06:14,200
I didn't even know.

164
00:06:14,200 --> 00:06:15,440
For a while now.

165
00:06:15,440 --> 00:06:17,440
Kree once told me that...

166
00:06:17,440 --> 00:06:18,120
Peck?

167
00:06:18,120 --> 00:06:19,240
Yeah.

168
00:06:19,240 --> 00:06:19,760
Who is she?

169
00:06:19,760 --> 00:06:22,080
Peck is a pilot.
After every flight,

170
00:06:22,080 --> 00:06:26,920
she invites all
the crew members out for drinks.

171
00:06:26,920 --> 00:06:27,520
Miss Sky...

172
00:06:27,520 --> 00:06:31,040
I think we should go
grab some more drinks.

173
00:06:31,040 --> 00:06:33,960
Let's drink until dawn.

174
00:06:34,560 --> 00:06:36,680
And what else?

175
00:06:36,680 --> 00:06:37,840
They have incredible hearing.

176
00:06:37,840 --> 00:06:39,840
Huh?

177
00:06:39,840 --> 00:06:42,400
You're definitely not on their side.

178
00:06:45,320 --> 00:06:48,960
Freeze!
Whoever moves is a dog!

179
00:06:50,200 --> 00:06:53,640
Holy shit!
Hey, Doctor Yep!

180
00:06:53,640 --> 00:06:55,920
Why are you so stiff?

181
00:06:55,920 --> 00:06:57,280
What did you just say?

182
00:06:57,280 --> 00:07:00,560
He said,
"Whoever moves is a dog."

183
00:07:00,560 --> 00:07:02,360
Hey, that means I'm a dog!

184
00:07:02,360 --> 00:07:03,120
His hearing is way too good.

185
00:07:03,120 --> 00:07:03,880
I am not a dog!

186
00:07:03,880 --> 00:07:05,240
You didn't tell me!
Why didn't you tell me first?

187
00:07:05,240 --> 00:07:07,360
Now, I look stupid.

188
00:07:07,880 --> 00:07:10,240
This is ridiculous. What kind
of game are you playing?

189
00:07:10,240 --> 00:07:12,400
Miss Sky, I think we should
go talk somewhere else.

190
00:07:12,400 --> 00:07:14,280
The vibe here is totally off.

191
00:07:14,280 --> 00:07:14,960
Yeah, true.

192
00:07:14,960 --> 00:07:15,520
Right?

193
00:07:15,520 --> 00:07:16,040
Yes.

194
00:07:16,040 --> 00:07:17,640
Where would you like to go?

195
00:07:17,640 --> 00:07:18,840
Let's go to...

196
00:07:18,840 --> 00:07:20,280
Damn, his hearing
is insanely good.

197
00:07:20,280 --> 00:07:21,240
I look like an idiot now.

198
00:07:21,240 --> 00:07:22,480
An idiot? How?

199
00:07:22,480 --> 00:07:23,920
I'm not the dog, you are!

200
00:07:23,920 --> 00:07:26,400
No, you're a dog,
and...you're a monkey too.

201
00:07:26,400 --> 00:07:28,240
Fine, I'll be a monkey.

202
00:07:28,240 --> 00:07:29,160
Ever heard of the "Monkey and Dog Show"?

203
00:07:29,160 --> 00:07:30,480
Were you even born yet?

204
00:07:30,480 --> 00:07:31,720
I guess not, Glasses.

205
00:07:31,720 --> 00:07:33,320
Man, trying to make an animal joke.

206
00:07:33,320 --> 00:07:33,920
Damn you!

207
00:07:33,920 --> 00:07:36,400
You're a dumbass.

208
00:07:36,400 --> 00:07:37,880
Have you completely lost it?

209
00:07:37,880 --> 00:07:39,080
Stop worrying about
this for a second.

210
00:07:39,080 --> 00:07:40,480
Look at that guy.

211
00:07:40,480 --> 00:07:42,080
He checks every single box.

212
00:07:43,200 --> 00:07:45,200
Yeah, actually, that's true.

213
00:07:52,520 --> 00:07:54,480
Morning, Nin-Nin.

214
00:07:54,480 --> 00:07:57,040
Did you sleep well last night?

215
00:07:57,040 --> 00:07:59,280
Are you awake yet?

216
00:08:02,040 --> 00:08:04,080
Waking up early, aren't we?

217
00:08:04,080 --> 00:08:08,080
Having your ex sleep over
sure gets you all excited.

218
00:08:08,360 --> 00:08:11,480
Well, I had someone sleep over
with me too, okay?

219
00:08:11,480 --> 00:08:14,120
Oh, Gift...

220
00:08:14,120 --> 00:08:15,440
Who the hell are you talking to?

221
00:08:15,440 --> 00:08:16,600
Sorry, Sky.

222
00:08:16,600 --> 00:08:17,960
You can go back to sleep.

223
00:08:19,240 --> 00:08:21,000
Thanks a lot for coming over
to keep me company.

224
00:08:21,000 --> 00:08:21,720
But I can't come over to sleep here

225
00:08:21,720 --> 00:08:23,560
every single night like Ninja, you know.

226
00:08:23,560 --> 00:08:26,040
Oh, come on,
it's just for a few days.

227
00:08:27,960 --> 00:08:29,600
But just you wait...

228
00:08:30,040 --> 00:08:31,720
I'm gonna make sure
he can't stand it.

229
00:08:32,080 --> 00:08:33,480
Just watch me.

230
00:08:35,160 --> 00:08:36,240
Gift...

231
00:08:36,760 --> 00:08:38,120
I'm seriously asking...

232
00:08:38,120 --> 00:08:39,160
who are you talking to?

233
00:08:40,360 --> 00:08:42,280
Our house is just like your house.

234
00:08:42,280 --> 00:08:44,120
Make yourself right at home.

235
00:08:44,120 --> 00:08:46,080
Right at home in my house?

236
00:08:46,080 --> 00:08:47,600
Oh, you're getting it now.

237
00:08:47,600 --> 00:08:51,080
Nobody messes up
my house except me.

238
00:08:51,080 --> 00:08:54,840
You're so dead.

239
00:08:54,840 --> 00:08:55,840
Gift...

240
00:08:58,760 --> 00:09:00,520
Everyone in this house
is losing their minds.

241
00:09:06,080 --> 00:09:06,960
Oh, Gift!

242
00:09:06,960 --> 00:09:08,280
Wow.

243
00:09:08,280 --> 00:09:10,080
Not only is it not messy...

244
00:09:10,080 --> 00:09:11,720
it's sparkling clean.

245
00:09:11,720 --> 00:09:13,440
There are even
flower decorations.

246
00:09:13,560 --> 00:09:15,400
This place is way more livable...

247
00:09:15,760 --> 00:09:18,720
When there's just us,
it was a total mess.

248
00:09:18,720 --> 00:09:19,600
But when this guy shows up,

249
00:09:19,600 --> 00:09:21,440
he's suddenly
Mr. perfect homemaker.

250
00:09:21,440 --> 00:09:23,000
I didn't do any of this.

251
00:09:23,000 --> 00:09:24,760
Come, come,
sit down, sit down.

252
00:09:25,200 --> 00:09:26,720
If you didn't do it,
then who did?

253
00:09:27,560 --> 00:09:28,640
This looks amazing.

254
00:09:28,640 --> 00:09:31,200
Anyone want some coffee?

255
00:09:32,800 --> 00:09:34,160
One serving, please!

256
00:09:34,880 --> 00:09:36,240
Make that two!

257
00:09:36,240 --> 00:09:37,800
Bring it on.

258
00:09:39,040 --> 00:09:40,920
How much is a drink here anyway?

259
00:09:40,920 --> 00:09:41,920
It's not expensive.

260
00:09:46,200 --> 00:09:47,560
Well, I'm just sleepy.

261
00:09:47,560 --> 00:09:49,560
You're not sleepy, you're just horny.

262
00:09:49,560 --> 00:09:51,560
Why is everyone
so stressed out this early?

263
00:09:51,560 --> 00:09:52,880
Do you guys not like dancing?

264
00:09:53,200 --> 00:09:54,360
Or do you just
not know how to dance?

265
00:09:55,000 --> 00:09:56,840
Hey! Who are you
saying can't dance?

266
00:09:56,840 --> 00:09:58,280
I'm just saying.

267
00:09:59,120 --> 00:10:01,760
Okay, that feels like a personal attack.

268
00:10:02,480 --> 00:10:04,160
Let's see what you've got then.

269
00:10:05,240 --> 00:10:07,480
I bet you didn't know

270
00:10:07,480 --> 00:10:11,080
I used to do
dance competitions, huh?

271
00:10:11,080 --> 00:10:12,360
Alright, viewers!

272
00:10:12,360 --> 00:10:14,200
The tension is building!

273
00:10:14,200 --> 00:10:15,400
The next round is...

274
00:10:15,400 --> 00:10:17,560
the Battle Round!

275
00:10:17,560 --> 00:10:20,280
Battle on!

276
00:10:20,280 --> 00:10:22,280
Three, four!

277
00:10:28,480 --> 00:10:30,120
She doesn't know
what she's doing.

278
00:10:30,120 --> 00:10:31,280
Clap your hands!

279
00:10:31,280 --> 00:10:33,280
Gift, that's completely
the wrong kind of dancing!

280
00:10:34,200 --> 00:10:38,040
Hey, believe it or not,
I actually competed before!

281
00:10:38,040 --> 00:10:40,400
Seacon Square Contest 2013!

282
00:10:40,400 --> 00:10:41,600
The Maboonkrong Sports Day!

283
00:10:41,600 --> 00:10:43,760
Hey, I won
an honorable mention, okay?

284
00:10:43,760 --> 00:10:45,200
Well, at least
they gave you a compliment.

285
00:10:45,200 --> 00:10:47,080
Better than them calling
you an absolute dumbass.

286
00:10:48,280 --> 00:10:49,240
Just go sit down.

287
00:10:49,240 --> 00:10:50,320
Let's watch a real pro.

288
00:10:51,360 --> 00:10:52,560
Please.

289
00:10:56,840 --> 00:10:58,600
Whoa!

290
00:10:59,120 --> 00:11:00,680
How the hell did he fit
that outfit underneath?

291
00:11:00,680 --> 00:11:02,240
Just watch.

292
00:11:02,240 --> 00:11:04,240
He's definitely going to do
a seductive dance for Chai.

293
00:11:14,840 --> 00:11:16,960
Would you like a drink?

294
00:11:16,960 --> 00:11:18,960
Give me ten.

295
00:11:22,200 --> 00:11:24,160
Here you go, ten drinks!

296
00:11:24,840 --> 00:11:26,440
Ooh, I'm so jealous.

297
00:11:26,440 --> 00:11:28,400
You have your very own
male host bar right at home.

298
00:11:28,920 --> 00:11:29,800
Thank you.

299
00:11:29,800 --> 00:11:31,400
You have to rehearse your shows...

300
00:11:31,400 --> 00:11:33,280
and you still cook for us too.

301
00:11:33,920 --> 00:11:35,440
You already know, right, Shiney...

302
00:11:35,440 --> 00:11:37,400
that I'm good at multitasking.

303
00:11:37,400 --> 00:11:38,960
In Thai, does that translate to...

304
00:11:38,960 --> 00:11:40,440
"riding multiple things well"?

305
00:11:41,800 --> 00:11:43,600
Is the food not to your liking?

306
00:11:43,600 --> 00:11:46,680
I only made things that Shiney likes.

307
00:11:46,680 --> 00:11:49,880
Oh, but this is
stir-fried bean sprouts.

308
00:11:51,200 --> 00:11:52,960
Don't you know that...

309
00:11:52,960 --> 00:11:54,040
Chai doesn't eat bean sprouts?

310
00:11:54,040 --> 00:11:56,160
This looks so delicious!
Wow!

311
00:11:56,160 --> 00:11:57,240
Wait a minute.

312
00:11:57,480 --> 00:11:59,400
Does he actually
like eating them or not?

313
00:12:00,200 --> 00:12:03,240
Chai just doesn't eat
raw bean sprouts.

314
00:12:03,240 --> 00:12:04,640
How is it, Chai?

315
00:12:04,640 --> 00:12:05,640
It's delicious.

316
00:12:13,360 --> 00:12:16,520
Are you still impressed
by my cooking?

317
00:12:18,840 --> 00:12:21,920
Chai, please don't go
back to eating leftovers...

318
00:12:21,920 --> 00:12:24,120
that have just been reheated.

319
00:12:24,120 --> 00:12:28,240
No matter what,
you can't mask that rancid taste.

320
00:12:28,240 --> 00:12:31,440
Are you sure
it's a rancid taste?

321
00:12:31,440 --> 00:12:33,560
Or is it a taste
you've been craving...

322
00:12:34,480 --> 00:12:35,200
because you're bored of the food...

323
00:12:35,200 --> 00:12:37,200
you have to eat every single day?

324
00:12:41,400 --> 00:12:43,040
Chai, you'd better just
make a choice right now...

325
00:12:43,040 --> 00:12:45,040
on what kind of food
you actually want to eat.

326
00:12:51,080 --> 00:12:54,080
What I like is...

327
00:12:54,080 --> 00:12:55,400
Tell her!

328
00:12:55,400 --> 00:12:56,960
Actually...

329
00:12:56,960 --> 00:12:57,720
I like...

330
00:12:57,920 --> 00:12:59,360
Don't keep me in suspense.

331
00:12:59,360 --> 00:13:00,320
I like...

332
00:13:00,320 --> 00:13:03,280
You like...

333
00:13:03,840 --> 00:13:05,800
I've always liked Man United.

334
00:13:07,040 --> 00:13:09,120
I like Man United so, so much.

335
00:13:09,760 --> 00:13:11,560
I probably can't bring myself
to like anyone else...

336
00:13:11,560 --> 00:13:12,800
except Man United.

337
00:13:18,600 --> 00:13:21,040
Gift, what are you spacing out for?

338
00:13:21,040 --> 00:13:23,760
Oh, the Man United match last night...

339
00:13:23,760 --> 00:13:24,600
was so good, wasn't it?

340
00:13:24,600 --> 00:13:25,480
Did you watch it?

341
00:13:25,480 --> 00:13:26,480
They did amazing.

342
00:13:26,480 --> 00:13:27,240
I thought they were going
to lose their touch.

343
00:13:27,240 --> 00:13:28,040
Right?

344
00:13:28,040 --> 00:13:28,680
They were awesome.

345
00:13:28,680 --> 00:13:30,120
And you're just sitting there,
spacing out.

346
00:13:30,120 --> 00:13:30,880
Who knows how far those two...

347
00:13:30,880 --> 00:13:32,200
have already gone with their flirting?

348
00:13:32,200 --> 00:13:35,040
Chai, you actually watch
this kind of stuff?

349
00:13:35,040 --> 00:13:36,680
I had no idea.

350
00:13:36,680 --> 00:13:37,320
Well, talking about these
things with someone...

351
00:13:37,320 --> 00:13:38,640
who doesn't know anything...

352
00:13:39,120 --> 00:13:40,080
isn't really any fun, is it?

353
00:13:40,080 --> 00:13:41,080
Right.

354
00:13:48,160 --> 00:13:49,840
Mr. Kree, focus.

355
00:13:49,840 --> 00:13:51,880
Pray to the sacred
spirits protecting you...

356
00:13:51,880 --> 00:13:52,560
before drawing a card.

357
00:13:52,560 --> 00:13:54,680
Now, pick one.

358
00:13:54,680 --> 00:13:56,520
Make sure your question
is crystal clear.

359
00:13:56,520 --> 00:13:57,960
Specify a timeframe.

360
00:13:57,960 --> 00:13:59,200
Just one card.

361
00:13:59,200 --> 00:14:00,960
Here's the first card.
Let's flip it over.

362
00:14:00,960 --> 00:14:02,640
Boom!

363
00:14:02,640 --> 00:14:05,680
Uh...am I going to get hurt?

364
00:14:05,680 --> 00:14:06,440
Not at all.

365
00:14:06,440 --> 00:14:08,200
You really don't know
how to read cards, do you?

366
00:14:08,200 --> 00:14:10,240
You have the chance to...

367
00:14:10,240 --> 00:14:10,840
Look at this!

368
00:14:10,840 --> 00:14:13,520
Turn thousands into millions!

369
00:14:13,520 --> 00:14:14,920
Millions? Oh!

370
00:14:14,920 --> 00:14:16,880
Investing thousands
and getting millions in return.

371
00:14:16,880 --> 00:14:17,840
Are we getting a fortune reading

372
00:14:17,840 --> 00:14:20,760
or just looking at a cartoon?

373
00:14:20,760 --> 00:14:22,360
Have you never had
your fortune told before?

374
00:14:22,360 --> 00:14:23,760
Have you ever even
seen Oracle cards?

375
00:14:23,760 --> 00:14:25,680
For the second card,
use your left hand.

376
00:14:25,680 --> 00:14:26,600
Okay.

377
00:14:26,600 --> 00:14:27,600
Boom! The second card.

378
00:14:27,600 --> 00:14:29,960
It's so clear.
Look closely at the picture.

379
00:14:30,720 --> 00:14:32,480
Whose picture is it?

380
00:14:32,480 --> 00:14:34,320
It means you are
incredibly narcissistic.

381
00:14:34,320 --> 00:14:36,680
This is a picture of
a handsome, rich guy.

382
00:14:36,680 --> 00:14:37,760
That's not me.

383
00:14:37,760 --> 00:14:38,920
But if you look at me
as a handsome guy,

384
00:14:38,920 --> 00:14:40,680
well, I don't know what to tell you.

385
00:14:41,280 --> 00:14:43,480
You need to invest with a rich person.

386
00:14:43,480 --> 00:14:47,600
So that means I'm going
to get money from a rich guy?

387
00:14:47,920 --> 00:14:49,480
No, no!

388
00:14:49,480 --> 00:14:52,280
But let me tell you,
when a card like this pops up...

389
00:14:52,280 --> 00:14:54,200
it's divine intervention.

390
00:14:54,200 --> 00:14:56,920
It means you, Kree,
need to invest in making merit.

391
00:14:56,920 --> 00:14:58,600
Making merit?

392
00:14:58,600 --> 00:15:02,320
Yes, you can co-host
a Robe-Offering Ceremony with me.

393
00:15:02,320 --> 00:15:03,360
Merit brings peace of mind.

394
00:15:03,360 --> 00:15:04,400
If you do it and it makes you feel good...

395
00:15:04,400 --> 00:15:05,800
your life will get better.

396
00:15:05,800 --> 00:15:09,400
Here, just make a donation
according to your faith.

397
00:15:09,400 --> 00:15:10,480
The more merit you accumulate,

398
00:15:10,480 --> 00:15:12,160
the more you'll get what you desire.

399
00:15:12,160 --> 00:15:14,040
I am enlightened.

400
00:15:14,040 --> 00:15:16,720
Kree, you are such a complete dumbass.

401
00:15:16,720 --> 00:15:17,240
Hey!

402
00:15:17,240 --> 00:15:17,840
You don't need to stay here.

403
00:15:17,840 --> 00:15:19,280
Come work with me instead.

404
00:15:19,280 --> 00:15:20,800
Go work with Mr. Paul.

405
00:15:20,800 --> 00:15:22,560
Mr. Paul? Who's that?

406
00:15:22,560 --> 00:15:24,360
My new boyfriend.

407
00:15:24,360 --> 00:15:26,200
He's super rich.

408
00:15:26,200 --> 00:15:29,520
He's not some
brainless guy like you.

409
00:15:29,520 --> 00:15:31,320
You're going to end up
completely broke and bankrupt.

410
00:15:31,320 --> 00:15:33,320
A sexy person like me
won't let you get away with this.

411
00:15:33,320 --> 00:15:34,120
Kree, follow me.

412
00:15:34,120 --> 00:15:34,280
Hey!

413
00:15:34,280 --> 00:15:35,000
Get up, Kree!

414
00:15:35,000 --> 00:15:36,080
Kree, get up!

415
00:15:36,080 --> 00:15:37,440
I'll take care of you myself.

416
00:15:37,440 --> 00:15:38,080
You tramp!

417
00:15:38,080 --> 00:15:39,360
What now?

418
00:15:40,080 --> 00:15:41,480
That's enough!

419
00:15:41,480 --> 00:15:43,360
Kree, get out! Kree!

420
00:15:43,640 --> 00:15:45,800
Get out!

421
00:15:45,800 --> 00:15:48,160
I can't unsee that.
I can't unsee that!

422
00:15:48,160 --> 00:15:51,400
Oh, I can't take this anymore.

423
00:15:51,400 --> 00:15:52,800
What the hell is wrong with you?

424
00:15:52,800 --> 00:15:54,080
Uh, yes, the two of you.

425
00:15:54,080 --> 00:15:55,520
Can I help you?

426
00:15:55,520 --> 00:15:57,640
Doctor, I was actually
just about to ask...

427
00:15:57,640 --> 00:16:00,080
I heard you have a joint-investment
merit project, right?

428
00:16:00,080 --> 00:16:03,160
Yes, I do have a joint-investment
merit project.

429
00:16:03,160 --> 00:16:04,160
So we're here to...

430
00:16:04,160 --> 00:16:05,120
You're here to make merit, right?

431
00:16:05,120 --> 00:16:05,960
We're here to get our faces done.

432
00:16:05,960 --> 00:16:06,720
Huh?

433
00:16:06,720 --> 00:16:07,680
As for the merit part,

434
00:16:07,680 --> 00:16:08,640
we just happened to hear about it.

435
00:16:08,640 --> 00:16:09,840
You guys? Coming here
to get your faces done?

436
00:16:09,840 --> 00:16:10,640
Yes, sir.

437
00:16:11,320 --> 00:16:12,480
Have you had any work done
on your face lately, Doctor?

438
00:16:12,480 --> 00:16:13,840
Not really, not anytime recently.

439
00:16:13,840 --> 00:16:15,080
I figured.

440
00:16:15,080 --> 00:16:16,280
Let me do yours first then, okay?

441
00:16:19,720 --> 00:16:21,560
Okay.

442
00:16:21,560 --> 00:16:23,880
But we have to wait for
the numbing cream to kick in.

443
00:16:23,880 --> 00:16:25,040
Please wait here for a moment.

444
00:16:25,040 --> 00:16:25,880
I'll be right back.

445
00:16:26,240 --> 00:16:26,760
Sure.

446
00:16:26,760 --> 00:16:28,000
Make yourself comfortable.

447
00:16:28,000 --> 00:16:29,400
Wait, what's with this shirt?

448
00:16:29,400 --> 00:16:31,040
My heart isn't locked or whatever?

449
00:16:31,040 --> 00:16:33,040
Did you look for this yourself?

450
00:16:33,040 --> 00:16:36,040
No, I already had it in my closet.

451
00:16:36,040 --> 00:16:37,640
What kind of person are you?

452
00:16:40,720 --> 00:16:41,360
Come on, Yoon.

453
00:16:41,360 --> 00:16:43,360
We've got a bit of time
before the doctor gets back.

454
00:16:50,960 --> 00:16:53,040
Oh, the room is locked.

455
00:16:53,040 --> 00:16:54,640
Please open the door for me!

456
00:16:54,640 --> 00:16:56,600
Doctor, we can't open it
from this side either.

457
00:16:56,600 --> 00:16:57,480
The door seems to be broken.

458
00:16:57,480 --> 00:16:58,560
Should I just break it down, Doctor?

459
00:16:58,560 --> 00:17:00,320
Hey, it's fine, it's fine!

460
00:17:00,320 --> 00:17:01,960
I'll go find the key instead.

461
00:17:01,960 --> 00:17:03,200
Just wait a little longer.

462
00:17:03,200 --> 00:17:04,320
Okay, okay.

463
00:17:04,320 --> 00:17:06,200
Hey, that's a good idea.

464
00:17:06,680 --> 00:17:08,040
Let me ask you something.

465
00:17:08,040 --> 00:17:08,400
Yeah?

466
00:17:08,400 --> 00:17:09,840
Why are you helping me anyway?

467
00:17:10,520 --> 00:17:11,720
Well, you're my host.

468
00:17:12,120 --> 00:17:14,240
Your problem is my problem.

469
00:17:16,080 --> 00:17:16,680
Damn.

470
00:17:16,680 --> 00:17:18,640
So, you have to split the reward

471
00:17:18,640 --> 00:17:20,440
for catching that spy with me.

472
00:17:20,440 --> 00:17:21,240
Well, yeah...

473
00:17:21,240 --> 00:17:24,160
Just think about how huge
the tip will be!

474
00:17:24,160 --> 00:17:26,520
We split it fifty-fifty, okay?

475
00:17:26,520 --> 00:17:28,400
Yeah, fifty-fifty.

476
00:17:28,400 --> 00:17:30,520
Hey, are you starting
to feel numb yet?

477
00:17:30,520 --> 00:17:32,520
Not really.
Are you?

478
00:17:32,520 --> 00:17:33,320
I don't know.

479
00:17:33,320 --> 00:17:36,720
I think I'm starting to feel numb.

480
00:17:36,720 --> 00:17:39,560
Let's keep searching!

481
00:17:39,560 --> 00:17:40,880
Are you seriously not numb yet?

482
00:17:44,400 --> 00:17:46,400
Mr. Yoon, Mr. All-New,
please wait a moment.

483
00:17:46,400 --> 00:17:48,080
I'm trying to open the door!

484
00:17:48,080 --> 00:17:50,040
Okay!

485
00:17:50,040 --> 00:17:52,040
Damn, we still haven't found it.

486
00:17:55,480 --> 00:17:57,200
Hey, I found a CD.

487
00:17:57,200 --> 00:17:59,480
Found a CD!

488
00:18:01,120 --> 00:18:03,120
Just one single CD?

489
00:18:09,520 --> 00:18:11,840
Oh! Finally!

490
00:18:12,840 --> 00:18:16,440
Alright, it's time.

491
00:18:16,440 --> 00:18:17,480
Doctor!

492
00:18:17,480 --> 00:18:18,920
We actually have
an urgent matter...

493
00:18:18,920 --> 00:18:20,560
so we have to
head out right now.

494
00:18:25,600 --> 00:18:27,920
Then let me wipe off
the numbing cream first.

495
00:18:31,360 --> 00:18:32,480
What the hell
did they just say?

496
00:18:35,600 --> 00:18:39,280
Gift, I found the guys
to help teach you about soccer.

497
00:18:39,280 --> 00:18:41,640
I texted them
and they showed up right away.

498
00:18:42,640 --> 00:18:46,560
Thanks a lot.
Ninja is so dead.

499
00:18:46,560 --> 00:18:48,480
I'm in your hands.

500
00:18:55,520 --> 00:18:59,520
Oh, they said today
is the "Red Derby" match.

501
00:18:59,800 --> 00:19:01,920
Man United vs. Liverpool.

502
00:19:01,920 --> 00:19:03,080
It doesn't mean anyone
is on their period, okay?

503
00:19:03,400 --> 00:19:05,480
Yeah, I know that!

504
00:19:05,480 --> 00:19:07,720
But they're both the same team,

505
00:19:07,720 --> 00:19:08,640
why are they playing
against each other?

506
00:19:08,640 --> 00:19:09,440
Huh?

507
00:19:09,440 --> 00:19:11,040
I mean, they both wear red.

508
00:19:11,040 --> 00:19:14,080
The Premier League isn't
a school sports day, idiot!

509
00:19:14,760 --> 00:19:16,960
All-New, Yoon, handle this.

510
00:19:20,800 --> 00:19:22,200
Stop!

511
00:19:22,200 --> 00:19:25,200
Help teach her,
we're not playing charades!

512
00:19:28,200 --> 00:19:30,760
Wait, do you honestly
think I get any of this?

513
00:19:41,200 --> 00:19:43,720
Gift, what is there
to be confused about?

514
00:19:43,720 --> 00:19:45,200
Even though I don't know
anything about soccer...

515
00:19:45,200 --> 00:19:46,640
I still know that
Liverpool scored.

516
00:19:46,640 --> 00:19:48,480
I don't even know
whose reaction to copy.

517
00:19:48,640 --> 00:19:49,760
I see Yoon celebrating

518
00:19:49,760 --> 00:19:50,800
and All-New looking devastated.

519
00:19:50,800 --> 00:19:51,880
What am I supposed to do?

520
00:19:51,880 --> 00:19:53,080
Look, look, do it like this.

521
00:19:53,080 --> 00:19:54,880
Do this, just follow my lead.

522
00:19:54,880 --> 00:19:57,280
Say Liverpool scores,
you go, "Yay!"

523
00:19:57,280 --> 00:19:59,440
Hey, Liverpool sucks!

524
00:19:59,440 --> 00:20:00,800
Liverpool sucks?

525
00:20:02,040 --> 00:20:05,120
Look, just cheer for
Man United like Chai does.

526
00:20:05,120 --> 00:20:06,000
I'll be right back.

527
00:20:06,000 --> 00:20:07,360
I'm going to see Doctor Yep
for a quick errand.

528
00:20:07,360 --> 00:20:09,400
Why are you getting
your face done right now?

529
00:20:09,400 --> 00:20:12,840
I've already been pretty
enough for this lifetime.

530
00:20:12,840 --> 00:20:14,960
My beauty is maxed out,
off the charts.

531
00:20:14,960 --> 00:20:17,440
I'm getting work done
for my next lifetime, okay?

532
00:20:18,080 --> 00:20:19,880
Just stay right here.

533
00:20:19,880 --> 00:20:21,920
I'm leaving her with you guys.

534
00:20:29,720 --> 00:20:31,400
What is so fun about this?

535
00:20:31,400 --> 00:20:33,800
Why are they so into it?

536
00:20:34,920 --> 00:20:35,960
Who is that guy?

537
00:20:36,480 --> 00:20:38,520
Ooh, he's so hot.

538
00:20:44,360 --> 00:20:46,000
I can't understand a word!

539
00:20:47,600 --> 00:20:49,440
Let me ask AI chat first.

540
00:20:49,840 --> 00:20:53,880
Ah...Mason Mount.

541
00:20:53,880 --> 00:20:57,880
Damn, he's gorgeous.

